ad Recently I watched #TheLittleThingsMovie and it was the best film I've seen for quite some time! I was so engrossed and it made such a big difference from binging shows every evening (which has become my go-to activity during lockdown) that the whole experience felt like a little refresher for me.

A little escapism into a story was just what I needed. This story is told so well and with plenty of room for guesses and interpretation. The ending in particular was not at all what I was expecting and that made it all the more satisfying.

Here are my thoughts, followed by the trailer. It's available to rent at home now and I can't recommend it highly enough! A massive thank you to @WarnerBrosUK for inviting me to see it and for choosing me to spread the word. www.WatchTheLittleThings.co.uk

Ad  Sunday lunch is served!

I wanted something wholesome because it's cold, wet 
and grey outside, but I'm also kickstarting 2021 with a healthy diet and trying to eat less meat.

I made @nakedgloryuk sausages with cauliflower mash, sticky red onion gravy and greens. Entirely plant-based, yet super succulent and meaty, whilst also being totally delicious!

Enjoy!

You can find #NakedGlory in most major supermarkets, as well as online.

Ad  Operation eat less meat is underway! My resolution this year is to double down on 2020's effort to reduce my impact on the environment, and that means a reduction in my meat consumption. 

But I do enjoy meat, so for this recipe, I’m getting the best of both worlds and using @Nakedgloryuk's Quarter Pounders. They've blown my mind! 

They have all the taste and texture of the real thing and even cook in the same way, so you don't have to alter your usual recipes to be better to the planet.

You can find the range in the plant-based section of most supermarkets and online. Give it a go.

(Side note, I used their Tasty Tenderstrips for Fajitas last night and I can confirm that they are incredible). #NakedGlory

Ad You might have seen on my page that I’m an ambassador for @GilletteUK’s partnership with @Movember this year and I’m super proud to be supporting such a worthwhile cause.
 
So, here’s how we can help change the face of men’s mental health: join me, shave down and Mo up this Movember to help support our frontline workers – it’s simple to sign up at Movember.com/Gillette.
 
There are loads of fun ways you can get involved but perhaps the easiest is by buying a special Gillette x Movember razor pack from @tescofood where one pack = one donation. It doesn’t matter what your Mo looks like (all Mo’s welcome – though I do have high hopes for mine), the important thing is that as many people as possible get involved because every Mo will raise awareness, it will raise funds, it will start a conversation and it may even save a life.
 
All through November, @GilletteUK will be raising awareness and funds for @Movember which this year, is more important than ever because the money raised will support the mental health of our key workers - the heroes who have kept us going during the pandemic. It’s time for us to look after them. I know this is something we all care deeply, so I’m challenging you to put your tash where your mouth is!
 
Gentlemen, start your razors.
 
#GilletteMovember #GentlemenLetsMo

I hung a couple of mirrors in the living room and we went to Richmond for brunch and a stroll by the river.

What have you been up to?

node.text:
Ad | gifted car seat. A Sunday well spent. 

Sarah is nearly 37 weeks - that’s full term and our baby could show up at any time from now, so I set up the @silvercrossuk Dream car seat. Then we went to @wackaespresso for breakfast, followed by a walk. Now it’s cookies and a little glass of @johnniewalker Blue Label while we cosy up.
Have a great evening, everyone x
